title: News Wrap: Gun rights protests greet Obama in Oregon PBS NewsHour
text: In our news wrap Friday, hundreds of gun rights demonstrators gathered near the airport in Roseburg, Oregon, as President Obama visited to console victims and families after a mass shooting at a community college. Meanwhile, shooting episodes broke out at universities in Texas and Arizona.
